course_content.core:
A-Level Structure 5 term course – August to July (Year 12) and August to final exams in May/June (Year 13)
All subjects except Further Maths students, Art, DT, PE: AS Level exams in June of Year 12 followed by full A Level exams in June of Year 13. 
Art, DT, PE – 1 set of exams at end of Year 13 with additional coursework components in Year 12 and Year 13. 
Further Maths students take Maths full A Level in Year 12 and full Further Maths in Year 13
Students choose 3 or 4 AS Level subjects in Year 12, followed by the same 3 or 4 subjects in Year 13.
AS Level is worth 50% of full A Level, Year 13 A Level exams worth 50% of final full A Level grade. 5 term course – August to July (Year 12) and August to final exams in May/June (Year 13) All subjects except Further Maths students, Art, DT, PE: AS Level exams in June of Year 12 followed by full A Level exams in June of Year 13. The programme is taught in two semesters over the nine months and is assessed via examinations (in both semesters) and coursework in the second semester.
